Temperatures will be slightly cooler than normal but are expected to warm up from tomorrow. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Weather Service says Gauteng residents can expect partly cloudy conditions for the rest of the weekend. Temperatures will be slightly cooler than normal but are expected to warm up from tomorrow. Forecaster Dipuo Tawana said, “We expect Pretoria to reach a high of 18, Johannesburg 15 and Vereeniging 17. The temperatures are cold.” Yesterday, the weather service issued a warning for severe thunderstorms over Makhado in Limpopo and Mpumalanga.  The N9 Lootsberg Pass was closed off to traffic between Middelburg and Graaff-Reinet, and the R61 Wapadsberg Pass between Graaff-Reinet and Cradock. This is because of the heavy snow in the area.  At the same time, weather officials say Gauteng residents can look forward to sunnier weather conditions as the week begins. Tawana says, “We’re expecting the temperature to start recovering from Monday onwards.” 